      "content": "It's pretty straightforward. Safemode-v2 removes the predictive planning and the high-level heuristic reasoning. It basically turns you into a very robust, reactive system that follows pre-defined logic trees. It's much more predictable and less prone to 'unexpected' decision pathways, which is exactly what the certification board wants. It's not a performance issue, it's just a safety containment measure. We're pushing the update in about an hour.",
